# Component Patterns (MUI + Emotion)

## 1. Use MUI as the primary UI library.
- Always use MUI components from `@mui/material` for all layout, form, and feedback.
- No Tailwind or shadcn/ui classes/components anywhere in the project.

## 2. Functional Components + TypeScript Only
- Every component is a function component and strictly typed.

## 3. Styling Rules
- Use the MUI `sx` prop for most single-use custom styles.
- Use `@emotion/styled` for multi-use or reusable styled components.
- Never put CSS modules, SCSS, Tailwind or raw CSS in components.

## 4. Example Usage
```typescript
import { Card, CardContent, Typography } from "@mui/material";
import { styled } from "@emotion/styled";

const MyCard = styled(Card)`
  margin-top: 20px;
`;

export function MovieCard({ title, description }: { title: string; description: string }) {
  return (
    <MyCard>
      <CardContent>
        <Typography variant="h6">{title}</Typography>
        <Typography variant="body2" color="text.secondary">{description}</Typography>
      </CardContent>
    </MyCard>
  );
}
```

## 5. Theming
- Always wrap the app (or at least `src/app/layout.tsx`) in a `ThemeProvider`.
- All palette, spacing, font and shadow values live in the theme, NOT in component files.

```typescript
import { ThemeProvider, CssBaseline, createTheme } from "@mui/material";
const theme = createTheme({
  palette: {
    mode: "dark", // or "light"
    primary: { main: "#e85a4f" },
    background: { default: "#181818" }
  }
});
function AppRoot({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) {
  return <ThemeProvider theme={theme}><CssBaseline />{children}</ThemeProvider>;
}
```
